#Text=Jack H.
#Text=Freed
#Text=Jack H. Freed
#Text=( born April 19 , 1938 ) is an American chemist known for his pioneering work in electron paramagnetic resonance ( aka electron spin resonance ) spectroscopy .
#Text=He is the Frank and Robert Laughlin Professor of Physical Chemistry , Emeritus , at Cornell University in Ithaca , New York .
#Text=Biography
#Text=Jack Freed was born in New York City .
#Text=He received his bachelor 's degree in chemical engineering in 1958 from Yale University and his Ph.D. in chemistry in 1962 from Columbia University .
#Text=Freed is currently the Frank and Robert Laughlin Professor of Physical Chemistry , Emeritus , in the Department of Chemistry and Chemical Biology at Cornell University . [ 1 ]

#Text=In 2001 , Freed founded the National Biomedical Center for Advanced Electron Spin Resonance Technology ( ACERT ) [ 2 ] funded by National Institutes of Health and has been its Director since then .
#Text=In 2004 , he was an editor for Journal of Physical Chemistry .

#Text=Before that he was a fellow in numerous places such as Alfred P. Sloan Research Foundation , American Academy of Arts and Sciences , American Physical Society , John Simon Guggenheim Memorial Foundation , Hebrew University Institute for Advanced Studies , and Weizmann Institute of Science .
#Text=Honors and awards
#Text=Fellow of the A. P. Sloan Foundation , 1966
#Text=Senior Fellow of the Weizmann Institute of Science , 1970
#Text=Fellow of the American Physical Society , 1976

#Text=Bruker Award in Electron Spin Resonance by the Royal Society of Chemistry , 1990
#Text=Fellow of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences , 1994
#Text=Gold Medal by International EPR/ESR Society , 1994 [ 4 ]
#Text=Irving Langmuir Prize in Chemical Physics by the American Physical Society , 1997 [ 5 ] [ 6 ]
#Text=International Zavoisky Award by the Russian Academy of Sciences , 1998 [ 7 ]
#Text=Honorary member of the National Magnetic Society of India , 2001
#Text=Special J.H. Freed Festschrift Issue by the Journal of Physical Chemistry on his 65th birthday , 2004 [ 8 ] [ 9 ]
#Text=Fellow of the International Society of Magnetic Resonance , 2008
#Text=E. Bright Wilson Award in Spectroscopy
#Text=by the American Chemical Society , 2008 [ 10 ] [ 11 ]

#Text=Fellow of the American Association for the Advancement of Science , 2009
#Text=ISMAR Prize by the International Society of Magnetic Resonance , 2013 [ 12 ]
#Text=Joel Henry Hildebrand Award in the Chemistry of Liquids by the American Chemical Society , 2014 [ 13 ] [ 14 ] [ 15 ] [ 16 ]
